6T SRAM Cell Design using Cadence Virtuoso
Overview

This project presents the design and simulation of a 6-Transistor Static Random Access Memory (6T SRAM) cell using Cadence Virtuoso. The design demonstrates fundamental memory cell behavior including read/write operations and stability analysis through DC simulations.

The 6T SRAM cell is widely used in modern memory architectures due to its high speed, low power consumption, and robust performance.

Tools & Technology
Cadence Virtuoso (Schematic & Simulation)
CMOS Technology (45nm / gpdk45)
Analog Design Environment (ADE)
DC Analysis
SRAM Cell Architecture

The 6T SRAM cell consists of:
2 Cross-Coupled Inverters (4 Transistors)
2 Access Transistors (controlled by Word Line - WL)
Key Nodes:
NODE-1 → Q
NODE-2 → Q̅
Control Signals:
WL → Word Line
BL → Bit Line
BLBAR → Complementary Bit Line
